Multiple Regression¶

   y = bo+ b1X1 + b2X2 + b3X3 + b4X4 + b5X5 + b6X6 + b7X7 + b8X8 + b9X9 + b10X10 + b11X11 + b12X12 + b13X13 + b14X14 + b15X15 + b16X16 + ei
where y is dependent variable ie., y= Sales
and Xi's are independent variable ie.,
                             b0=Intercept
X1=Category_coded               b1=coefficient of X1(=Category_coded)
X2=City_coded                   b2=coefficient of X2(=City_coded) 
X3=Credit_Days                  b3=coefficient of X3(=Credit_Days) 
X4=Customer_ID_coded            b4=coefficient of X4(=Customer_ID_coded)
X5=Discount_inPercentage        b5=coefficient of X5(=Discount_inPercentage)
X6=Order_Date                   b6=coefficient of X6(=Order_Date) 
X7=Order_ID                     b7=coefficient of X7(=Order_ID) 
X8=Product_Name                 b8=coefficient of X8(=Product_Name)   
X9=Quantity                     b9=coefficient of X9(=Quantity)  
X10=Region_coded                b10=coefficient of X10(=Region_coded) 
X11=Sales_Person_ID_coded       b11=coefficient of X11(=Sales_Person_ID_coded) 
X12=Ship_Mode_coded             b12=coefficient of X12(=Ship_Mode_coded) 
X13=State_coded                 b13=coefficient of X13(=State_coded) 
X14=Sub_Category_coded          b14=coefficient of X14(=Sub_Category_coded)
X15=Unit_Price                  b15=coefficient of X15(=Unit_Price)
X16=year_month_coded            b16=coefficient of X16(=year_month_coded)

To Test: (i) H0: Beta(i) = 0 vs. H1: Beta(i) != 0 where i=0,1,...,16.

(ii) H0: Model is not significant vs. H1: Model is significant

Critical Region :If pvalue<0.05, so we reject our null hypothesis at 5% level of significance.

Instead of arbitrarily choosing alpha = 1 , it would be better to use cross-validation to choose the tuning parameter alpha. We can do this using the cross-validated ridge regression function, RidgeCV().

Multiple Regression¶

   y = bo+ b1X1 + b2X2 + b3X3 + b4X4 + b5X5 + b6X6 + b7X7 + b8X8 + b9X9 + b10X10 + b11X11 + b12X12 + b13X13 + b14X14 + b15X15 + b16X16 + ei
where y is dependent variable ie., y= Sales
and Xi's are independent variable ie.,
                             b0=Intercept
X1=Technology                b1=coefficient of X1(=Technology)
X2=OfficeSupplies            b2=coefficient of X2(=OfficeSupplies) 
X3=Furniture                 b3=coefficient of X3(=Furniture) 
X4=City_coded                b4=coefficient of X4(=City_coded)
X5=Customer_ID_coded         b5=coefficient of X5(=Customer_ID_coded)
X6=Discount_inPercentage     b6=coefficient of X6(=Discount_inPercentage) 
X7=Quantity                  b7=coefficient of X7(=Quantity) 
X8=East                      b8=coefficient of X8(=East)   
X9=West                      b9=coefficient of X9(=West)  
X10=South                    b10=coefficient of X10(=South) 
X11=North                    b11=coefficient of X11(=North) 
X12=Central                  b12=coefficient of X12(=Central) 
X13=Segment_coded            b13=coefficient of X13(=Segment_coded) 
X14=Sub_Category_coded       b14=coefficient of X14(=Sub_Category_coded)
X15=Unit_Price               b15=coefficient of X15(=Unit_Price)
X16=year_month_coded         b16=coefficient of X16(=year_month_coded)

To Test: (i) H0: Beta(i) = 0 vs. H1: Beta(i) != 0 where i=0,1,...,16.

(ii) H0: Model is not significant vs. H1: Model is significant

Critical Region :If pvalue<0.05, so we reject our null hypothesis at 5% level of significance.
